---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Schedule from '../../components/Schedule';
---

<Base title="MMA" description="MMA classes at Lions MMA Vancouver. Striking into grappling, grappling into striking. Led by Amir Ghassemi and Rodrigo Sezinando.">

  <!-- Full-width hero image with text overlay -->
  <div class="relative w-full h-[280px] md:h-[520px] overflow-hidden">
    <!-- Image placeholder (swap for real <img> when photos arrive) -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-iron/60 flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-3">
      <svg class="w-10 h-10 text-smoke/20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M23 19a2 2 0 01-2 2H3a2 2 0 01-2-2V8a2 2 0 012-2h4l2-3h6l2 3h4a2 2 0 012 2v11z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/><circle cx="12" cy="13" r="4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/></svg>
      <p class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-widest text-smoke/30 uppercase">Image Coming Soon</p>
    </div>
    <!-- Dark overlay so text is readable -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-void/50"></div>
    <!-- Nav spacer + text pinned to bottom-left -->
    <div class="relative z-10 h-full flex flex-col justify-end pb-14 px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-20 max-w-7xl mx-auto w-full" style="padding-top: 96px;">
      <p class="font-mono text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-canvas/60 mb-4">TRAIN LIKE A PRO</p>
      <h1 class="font-display text-[clamp(3.5rem,7vw,7rem)] uppercase tracking-tight text-canvas leading-none">MMA.</h1>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Content -->
  <div class="py-24 max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6">

    <!-- What it is -->
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-16 mb-24">
      <div>
        <p class="font-mono text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-smoke border-b border-iron pb-2 mb-8">WHAT IT IS</p>
        <div class="space-y-6 font-body text-canvas/80 leading-relaxed">
          <p>Mixed Martial Arts is what happens when every discipline matters. You train Muay Thai, you train BJJ, you train wrestling, and then you put them in the same round and figure out how they talk to each other. The striking threat sets up the takedown. The takedown threat opens the striking. The guard becomes a weapon. Every transition is both a danger and an opportunity.</p>
          <p>MMA classes at Lions are led by Amir Ghassemi and Rodrigo Sezinando, a striking specialist and a BJJ black belt with deep MMA coaching experience, respectively. The curriculum is built around the transitions: striking to clinch, clinch to takedown, takedown defense into counters, top control into ground-and-pound.</p>
          <p>MMA classes are not beginner classes. Students are expected to have a working foundation in at least one discipline, striking or grappling, before stepping into MMA-specific training. The gym is happy to help you build that foundation first. When you are ready, this is where the full picture comes together.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-6">
        <div class="flex-1 min-h-52 bg-iron/30 border border-iron flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-3">
          <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-smoke/30" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M23 19a2 2 0 01-2 2H3a2 2 0 01-2-2V8a2 2 0 012-2h4l2-3h6l2 3h4a2 2 0 012 2v11z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/><circle cx="12" cy="13" r="4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/></svg>
          <p class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-widest text-smoke/40 uppercase">Image Coming Soon</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex-1 min-h-52 bg-iron/30 border border-iron flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-3">
          <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-smoke/30" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M23 19a2 2 0 01-2 2H3a2 2 0 01-2-2V8a2 2 0 012-2h4l2-3h6l2 3h4a2 2 0 012 2v11z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/><circle cx="12" cy="13" r="4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/></svg>
          <p class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-widest text-smoke/40 uppercase">Image Coming Soon</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Who it is for -->
    <div class="mb-20 max-w-4xl">
      <p class="font-mono text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-smoke border-b border-iron pb-2 mb-8">WHO IT IS FOR</p>
      <ul class="space-y-3 font-body text-canvas/80 leading-relaxed">
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-brass font-mono text-xs mt-1 shrink-0">+</span><span>Strikers who want to understand what happens once a fight hits the ground</span></li>
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-brass font-mono text-xs mt-1 shrink-0">+</span><span>Grapplers who need to defend strikes and create takedowns off the cage</span></li>
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-brass font-mono text-xs mt-1 shrink-0">+</span><span>Fighters preparing for amateur or professional MMA competition</span></li>
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-brass font-mono text-xs mt-1 shrink-0">+</span><span>Athletes who want to train with a complete, cohesive game in mind</span></li>
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-brass font-mono text-xs mt-1 shrink-0">+</span><span>Students who have built a base in striking and grappling and are ready to combine them</span></li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- 3-image gallery strip -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-24">
      {[1,2,3].map(() => (
        <div class="h-56 bg-iron/30 border border-iron flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-3">
          <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-smoke/30" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M23 19a2 2 0 01-2 2H3a2 2 0 01-2-2V8a2 2 0 012-2h4l2-3h6l2 3h4a2 2 0 012 2v11z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/><circle cx="12" cy="13" r="4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/></svg>
          <p class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-widest text-smoke/40 uppercase">Image Coming Soon</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <!-- What a class looks like -->
    <div class="mb-16 max-w-4xl">
      <p class="font-mono text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-smoke border-b border-iron pb-2 mb-8">WHAT A CLASS LOOKS LIKE</p>
      <p class="font-body text-canvas/80 leading-relaxed">MMA classes are structured around one transition or scenario per session, for example, the clinch entry off a jab, or takedown defense into a counter-attack sequence. Warm-ups involve combinations that span striking and movement. Drilling covers the technical sequence at progressive speed. Classes close with MMA-specific sparring: standing exchanges, clinch work, and ground scenarios as appropriate for the group. The pace is high. The learning density is higher.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Wide image -->
    <div class="w-full h-64 bg-iron/30 border border-iron flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-3 mb-24">
      <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-smoke/30" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M23 19a2 2 0 01-2 2H3a2 2 0 01-2-2V8a2 2 0 012-2h4l2-3h6l2 3h4a2 2 0 012 2v11z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/><circle cx="12" cy="13" r="4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/></svg>
      <p class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-widest text-smoke/40 uppercase">Image Coming Soon</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Schedule -->
    <div class="mb-16">
      <p class="font-mono text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-smoke border-b border-iron pb-2 mb-8">CLASS SCHEDULE</p>
      <Schedule client:load filterDiscipline="mma" compact={true} />
    </div>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <div class="border border-iron p-10 flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-start sm:items-center justify-between gap-6">
      <div>
        <p class="font-display text-2xl uppercase text-canvas">Try it free.</p>
        <p class="font-mono text-xs text-smoke mt-1">7 days. No commitment.</p>
      </div>
      <a href="/free-trial" class="inline-block bg-brass text-void font-mono text-xs tracking-widest uppercase px-8 py-4 hover:bg-canvas transition-colors duration-200">
        CLAIM FREE TRIAL
      </a>
    </div>

  </div>
</Base>
